HEADWORD: black-tie
<hw>black-tie</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>requiring semiformal evening
clothes, e. g. a black bowtie and a tuxedo or dinner jacket for men, and
a formal dress for women; contrasted with <contr>white-tie</contr>, for
a fully formal occasion, and with <contr>informal</contr>, and
<contr>casual</contr>.</def> <illu>a <ex>black-tie</ex>
dinner</illu>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> semi-formal, semiformal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

